hands_on_practices.solution:
1. 平均能损：
$$\langle dE/dx\rangle_1 = A\ln(\xi^2+1)+B,\qquad 
\langle dE/dx\rangle_2 = A\ln\bigl((\xi/\alpha)^2+1\bigr)+B.$$

2. 差值：
$$\Delta=\langle dE/dx\rangle_1-\langle dE/dx\rangle_2
= A\Bigl[\ln(\xi^2+1)-\ln\bigl(\tfrac{\xi^2}{\alpha^2}+1\bigr)\Bigr]
= A\ln\!\frac{\xi^2+1}{\xi^2/\alpha^2+1}.$$

3. 平均值：
\begin{align*}
\overline{\langle dE/dx\rangle}
&=\tfrac12\Bigl(\langle dE/dx\rangle_1+\langle dE/dx\rangle_2\Bigr)\\
&=\tfrac A2\Bigl[\ln(\xi^2+1)+\ln\bigl(\tfrac{\xi^2}{\alpha^2}+1\bigr)\Bigr]+B\\
&=A\Bigl[\tfrac12\bigl(\ln(\xi^2+1)+\ln(\tfrac{\xi^2}{\alpha^2}+1)\bigr)+\eta\Bigr].
\end{align*}

4. Nσ 条件：
$$\Delta = N\,\sigma_{dE/dx},\qquad R=\frac{\sigma_{dE/dx}}{\overline{\langle dE/dx\rangle}}.$$

5. 求解 R：
$$R=\frac{\Delta}{N\,\overline{\langle dE/dx\rangle}}
=\frac{A\ln\!\frac{\xi^2+1}{\xi^2/\alpha^2+1}}
{N\,A\Bigl[\frac12(\ln(\xi^2+1)+\ln(\tfrac{\xi^2}{\alpha^2}+1))+\eta\Bigr]}
=\frac{\ln\!\frac{\xi^2+1}{\xi^2/\alpha^2+1}}
{N\Bigl[\tfrac12\bigl(\ln(\xi^2+1)+\ln(\tfrac{\xi^2}{\alpha^2}+1)\bigr)+\eta\Bigr]}\,. $$

1. 带电入射粒子（电荷 $ze$）的冲量：
$$\Delta p_{\rm el}=e\int_{-\infty}^\infty E_y(t)\,dt
=e\int\frac{ze\,\gamma b}{\bigl(b^2+(\gamma vt)^2\bigr)^{3/2}}\,dt.$$
令 $u=\gamma vt$，则 $dt=du/(\gamma v)$：
$$\Delta p_{\rm el}
=e\,ze\int\frac{\gamma b}{(b^2+u^2)^{3/2}}\frac{du}{\gamma v}
=\frac{ze^2b}{v}\int_{-\infty}^\infty\frac{du}{(b^2+u^2)^{3/2}}.$$
使用积分 $\int_{-\infty}^\infty du/(b^2+u^2)^{3/2}=2/b^2$：
$$\Delta p_{\rm el}
=\frac{ze^2b}{v}\cdot\frac{2}{b^2}
=\frac{2ze^2}{v\,b}.$$

2. 磁单极子（磁荷 $g$）的冲量：
$$\Delta p_{\rm mon}
=e\int_{-\infty}^\infty E_z(t)\,dt
=e\int\frac{g\,v\gamma b}{(b^2+(\gamma vt)^2)^{3/2}}\,dt
=\frac{egv b}{v}\int\frac{du}{(b^2+u^2)^{3/2}}
=\frac{2eg}{b}.$$

3. 冲量之比：
$$\frac{\Delta p_{\rm mon}}{\Delta p_{\rm el}}
=\frac{2eg/b}{2ze^2/(v\,b)}
=\frac{v\,g}{z\,e},\qquad z=1\ (\text{质子}).$$

4. 阻止本领 ∝$(\Delta p)^2$，所以
$$\frac{(dE/dx)_{\rm mon}}{(dE/dx)_{\rm p}}
=\Bigl(\frac{v\,g}{e}\Bigr)^2.$$

5. Dirac量子化条件 $eg=2\pi\hbar\implies g/e=2\pi\hbar/e^2$。并且有 $e^2=4\pi\alpha\hbar$：
$$\Bigl(\frac{v\,g}{e}\Bigr)^2 = v^2 \Bigl(\frac{2\pi\hbar}{e^2}\Bigr)^2 = v^2 \Bigl(\frac{2\pi\hbar}{4\pi\alpha\hbar}\Bigr)^2 = v^2 \Bigl(\frac{1}{2\alpha}\Bigr)^2 = \frac{v^2}{4\alpha^2}.$$
